comments: "The World Needs a Drink" was recorded in 2005 and sent out on an advance promo album CD called "Honky Tonk Songs".  The actual album released in November 2005 ended up being called "Life Goes On" and didn't include "The World Needs a Drink".  The song wasn't released as a single, but still hit #26 on the country charts in November 2005 based off DJ airplay from the promo disc. The following year the label released "Best of Terri Clark: The Millenium Collection" and included this song.
